animisa：animisa（ti）
အနိမိသ（တိ）
[na+nimisa]
[န+နိမိသ]
Animisa，（adj.） [Ved. animeṣa，cp. nimisati] not winking，waking，watchful Dāvs v.26 （nayana）. （Page 33）

Animisa：The shrine built on the spot where the Buddha spent a week after the Enlightenment，gazing unwinking at the seat at the foot of the Bodhi tree，the seat of his great victory.

It was to the north of the Bodhi tree. J.i.77.
